comments:
@travelforphoebe I feel really ashamed for what you had to go through in India! Unfortunately, such desperate, mindless & unethical behaviours are an overall exhibition of a lot of factors starting from showing white girls(Westerners) as background item dancers in our domestic film industries, to porn & Russian escorts business. The parts you travelled(North India) are anyway not safe for any female, forget foreigners. 

One piece of suggestion: Now a days, you have social media. Why don't you try to make some genuine contacts in India? I think that's profitable for you from all ends! Get going with young Indians who are easy mixing & aware about the western world & cultures, they will not only help you find safe places & passes, but such contacts will also help avoid unnecessary expenses & explore India without this harassment! An insta friend of mine, a girl(German) is suppose to visit India in 2024. She is making her own arrangements but has confirmed to stay in touch. I think that's the most prudent thing to do!

Also, if you ever come to Kolkata(East India), you might find the people different. As I live here, I can say with certainty, people have a sense of self respect & maturity that prevents from such hankering & desperate behaviours!
